==English==

{{rank|received|read|together|301|already|son|death|works}}

===Etymology===
[[All]] ({{OE.}} ''al'') + [[ready]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ɔːlˈrɛdi/
*{{audio|en-us-already.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adverb===
'''already'''

#[[Prior]] to some specified [[time]], either past, present, or future; by this time; [[previously]]. 
#:''It was already [[dusk]], and the lamps were just being lighted as we paced up and down in front of Briony Lodge, waiting for the coming of its occupant.'' &mdash;Doyle
#An addition used to emphasize [[impatience]].
#:''I wish they'd finish, '''already''' so we can get going.''


====Usage note====
'''Already''' may be used with the [[past perfect]] (''I have already done that''), the [[future perfect]] (''When you arrive, the business will already have been completed'') as well as the [[simple future]] (''When you arrive, the business will already be complete'').
